title: Firefox Lag and Video Stuttering on StudyStream Website with Multiple Video Streams
content:
While using the StudyStream website on Mozilla Firefox, I’m experiencing significant performance issues when multiple users have their cameras turned on.

Symptoms include: 

   Real-time video lags and stutters noticeably. 
   Video feeds take several seconds to load or appear. 
   The stream is not smooth, making the experience frustrating during group sessions.

Additional Notes: 

   This issue only occurs on Firefox. The same website works smoothly with no noticeable lag on other browsers such as Google Chrome and Microsoft Edge. 
   My Firefox is updated to the latest version. 
   The problem persists even after disabling extensions and trying in a private window.

It appears that Firefox may be struggling with handling multiple simultaneous video streams on this specific site. Any guidance or fixes would be appreciated.
creator: aryanpunia0078
